column5: Seeing and enjoying the bird population gives hope that these species are still abundant. Bill
Good morning from Red Lake Rd.One of our 6 ruffed grouse that come daily.
We do feed the birds.Grouse like the buds on the birch trees but they are also eating the corn and oats we put out.Woodpeckers like the pork fat.
If there was a nice chunk of prime rib in that feeder,I'd be giving that woodpecker alittle competition!
Only prime rib here is in my freezer.And might see the BBQ.
That's a downy.Pic makes it look bigger.we do have the piliated ones now those are huge.Little entertainment while waiting for some warmer weather.-30 again this morning.
I get the downy woodpeckers here in Indiana. remember the hairy woodpecker is very similar to the downy, but much larger. people often get the 2 confused.
